3 Section 3. Section 13-14-112, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "13-14-112. Declarations for nomination -- fee -- filing. (1) Nonpartisan candidates shall file
5 declarations for nomination as required by the primary election laws in a form prescribed by the secretary of
6 state except as provided in 13-14-113. Except for a candidate covered under 7-1-205, a candidate may not file
7 for more than one public office.
8 (2) Declarations may not indicate political affiliation. The candidate may not state in the declaration
9 any principles or measures that the candidate advocates or any slogans.
10 (3) (a) The declaration for nomination must include a question that the candidate is required to
11 complete about whether the candidate has citizenship of any country other than the United States or is a
12 member of a federally recognized Indian tribe. The question must also require the candidate to list their other
13 country or countries of citizenship, as applicable.
14 (b) The information required in subsection (3)(a) must be posted online in a publicly available place
15 by the secretary of state.
16 (4) Each individual filing a declaration shall pay the fee prescribed by law for the office that the
17 individual seeks.
18 (5) Declarations must be filed:
19 (a) in the office of the secretary of state or the appropriate election administrator as provided in 13-
20 10-201; and
21 (b) within the filing period provided in 13-10-201(7) for the office that the individual seeks."
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Notification to tribal governments. The secretary of state shall send a
24 copy of [this act] to each federally recognized tribal government in Montana.
